	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65542610"><p>You're not being too picky. The summary pretends there's only one temperature in play, whereas the original source mentions at least two temperatures (one defined after a phonon-phonon equilibration time; and a more conventional thermodynamical temperature which is only well-defined after a longer time). The sensationalism comes from thinking the longer-time-scale one applies at very short time-scales.<br>It's shit like that which makes headlines and then makes people distrust research.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65542610">

